{
  "name": "Infestation",
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You cause a cloud of mites, fleas, and other parasites to appear momentarily on one creature you can see within range. The target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw, or it takes [[/r 1d6]] poison damage and moves 5 feet in a random direction if it can move and its speed is at least 5 feet. Roll a [[/r d4]] for the direction: 1, north; 2, south; 3, east; or 4, west. This movement doesn't provoke opportunity attacks, and if the direction rolled is blocked, the target doesn't move.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div><p>The spell's damage increases by [[/r 1d6]] when you reach 5th level ([[/r 2d6]]), 11th level ([[/r 3d6]]), and 17th level ([[/r 4d6]]).</p></div>",
